07:16.490 --> 07:18.910
Those shoes are awesome!

07:18.910 --> 07:21.500
I still only have the school-issued gym shoes.

07:21.810 --> 07:23.670
They're hand-me-downs.

07:23.670 --> 07:26.300
I'm using my brother's until I get new ones next week.

07:26.300 --> 07:28.210
Your brother plays volleyball too?

07:28.940 --> 07:32.120
He plays at a real powerhouse high school called Karasuno.

07:32.120 --> 07:35.330
He's like the ace.

07:35.330 --> 07:37.600
Th-The ace of a powerhouse?!

07:37.600 --> 07:39.680
Th-That's so awesome!

07:39.680 --> 07:42.690
N-Not really. It's not that big of a deal.

07:42.690 --> 07:44.230
He was the ace in junior high too.

07:44.230 --> 07:45.400
Wow!

07:45.990 --> 07:47.320
How long has he been playing?

07:47.320 --> 07:48.570
Did he play on this team?

07:48.570 --> 07:51.110
Aces are so cool!

07:53.250 --> 07:54.570
I'm home.

07:56.100 --> 07:58.040
Did your practice match today go well?

07:58.400 --> 07:59.950
Yeah, it went great!

07:59.950 --> 08:01.250
I scored a ton!

08:01.900 --> 08:03.760
That's cool.

08:06.500 --> 08:07.750
Let's practice passing.

08:07.750 --> 08:09.160
After we're done eating.

08:13.660 --> 08:14.720
Yamaguchi.

08:13.980 --> 08:15.340
What's the next class?

08:15.340 --> 08:16.430
Japanese!

08:16.070 --> 08:19.310
I'm gonna go to Karasuno's match tomorrow. Do you wanna come too?

08:16.430 --> 08:18.170
What, it's Japanese?

08:20.120 --> 08:22.770
My brother keeps telling me not 
to come because he gets nervous,

08:22.770 --> 08:26.980
but since my brother's a third-year, 
this will be the last match he plays in the prefecture.

08:26.980 --> 08:28.000
I'll go!

08:28.000 --> 08:30.530
I've never seen Akiteru play.

08:30.530 --> 08:33.320
Tsukishima, your brother's on 
Karasuno's volleyball team too?

08:33.320 --> 08:34.740
So is mine.

08:35.070 --> 08:37.120
What position does your brother play?

08:37.120 --> 08:38.410
Wing spiker.

08:38.410 --> 08:40.310
Hey! So does mine.

08:40.310 --> 08:43.210
They have a deep roster, so it's always really tough.

08:43.210 --> 08:47.290
If you can't even play in matches, you really have to wonder if going to a powerhouse school is worth it.

08:48.450 --> 08:50.880
Tsukki's brother plays in the matches.

08:51.360 --> 08:52.630
What? No way.

08:53.210 --> 08:58.430
I saw a match recently, 
and no one named Tsukishima was on the roster.

09:00.960 --> 09:02.890
That's impossible.

09:02.890 --> 09:05.310
I hear about the matches all the time.

09:05.310 --> 09:06.730
You're probably just mistaken.

09:08.080 --> 09:09.980
