10:42.070 --> 10:43.450
<i>How lame.</i>

10:54.120 --> 10:56.560
<i>It was just a high school club,</i>

10:56.560 --> 10:59.820
<i>but for me, that team and volleyball felt like they were everything my brother stood for.</i>

11:00.820 --> 11:03.300
<i>In the end, it made him tell pointless lies.</i>

11:04.220 --> 11:05.560
So you're the ace!

11:06.260 --> 11:07.180
Yep!

11:08.280 --> 11:11.580
<i>But he was probably trying to believe in it himself.</i>

11:12.310 --> 11:14.110
<i>That if he tried hard enough, it would come true.</i>

11:15.560 --> 11:17.280
<i>But so what if it did?</i>

11:17.800 --> 11:20.450
<i>Would it be worth the struggle?</i>

11:24.400 --> 11:27.690
Tsukki!

11:31.470 --> 11:32.210
What?

11:33.570 --> 11:38.340
You've always handled everything in a cool and smart way.

11:39.130 --> 11:42.110
I was always jealous of you.

11:43.460 --> 11:44.350
And?

11:48.100 --> 11:50.430
But lately, you're just lame!

11:52.080 --> 11:55.110
So what if Hinata might become the Little Giant some day?

11:55.540 --> 11:59.190
That only means you have to beat him, Tsukki!

11:59.190 --> 12:03.450
You should prove with your skill
 that you're better than Hinata is!

12:04.280 --> 12:07.200
You have the height, brains, and instinct,

12:07.200 --> 12:10.410
so why did you decide that improving is impossible?!

12:15.950 --> 12:22.800
Even if I worked really hard and became the best 
player on the team, what would happen after that?

12:23.920 --> 12:28.180
Even if we somehow made it to nationals, 
what comes next?

12:29.070 --> 12:31.460
There's always someone better.

12:31.460 --> 12:33.600
Even if you're able to show some results somewhere,

12:33.930 --> 12:36.060
you'll never actually be number one!

12:36.060 --> 12:37.610
You're gonna lose eventually!

12:38.020 --> 12:42.200
Everyone knows that, so how can they keep going?!

12:53.540 --> 12:58.110
What the hell do you need besides your own pride?!

13:11.420 --> 13:15.270
I never imagined this day would come.

13:24.300 --> 13:26.910
When the hell did you get so cool?

13:27.780 --> 13:29.530
You're really cool.

13:30.370 --> 13:33.120
T-Tsukki? What's wrong?

13:31.260 --> 13:35.660
<i>At the very least, it's better than my worn-out train of thought.</i>

13:36.430 --> 13:38.540
But I'm not convinced by that.

13:38.540 --> 13:39.290
Huh?

13:40.420 --> 13:41.500
I'm gonna go ask something.

13:42.600 --> 13:43.460
Tsukki?!

13:47.080 --> 13:48.510
You know, Daichi...

13:48.800 --> 13:49.550
Yeah?

13:49.550 --> 13:51.990
You sure it's okay to leave Tsukishima alone?

13:51.990 --> 13:55.420
If we force him to do it, it won't be personal training.

13:55.420 --> 13:56.980
